  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate given the amount stolen and the lack of a criminal history. The outburst in the courtroom was disregarded as it does not reflect the legal facts of the case. A period of six months is sufficient to serve as a punitive measure and a deterrent, acknowledging both the severity of the theft and the mitigating factors.",
